  <bodyText><![CDATA[<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><img src="/media/13067823/cycling-holidays-in-the-lakes-and-mountains-inghams.jpg" alt="taormina amphitheatre in italy" data-udi="umb://media/3d447fcd145244e793fd64ab0fbc0a40" /></p>
<p><span class="geolocation-title">An opportunity to discover the beauty of Sicily with a relaxing stay in Taormina, followed by visits to the baroque cities of the South East. <br /></span></p>
<p><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 1 </span><br />Fly to Catania and transfer to your hotel. In the evening, meet your fellow travellers and tour guide for a welcome drink.</p>
<p><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 2 <br /></span>Today, get to know the lovely seaside town of <a data-udi="umb://document/919b72992bd64fd4a35a60df994feff6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/919b72992bd64fd4a35a60df994feff6}" title="Taormina Area">Taormina</a> on a walking tour. You’ll get to see the Greco Roman amphitheatre with stunning views towards Mount Etna before enjoying an afternoon at leisure to explore the town at your own pace.</p>
<p><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 3 <br /></span>Mount Etna is Europe's highest active volcano and you’ll ascend to 1,900 metres today. In the afternoon, you’ll see the typical Sicilian town of Savoca, which formed the backdrop to the film The Godfather.<br /><span><br /><img src="/media/13067823/cycling-holidays-in-the-lakes-and-mountains-inghams.jpg" alt="View of Mount Etna in Sicily" data-udi="umb://media/3d447fcd145244e793fd64ab0fbc0a40" /><br /></span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 4 <br /></span>A day at leisure to relax and enjoy the hotel pool or perhaps the beach.</p>
<p><span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 5 <br /></span>Today </span>we travel southwards to visit <a data-udi="umb://document/74958cf24d8e4a73a918ab9166f47bcc" href="/{localLink:umb://document/74958cf24d8e4a73a918ab9166f47bcc}" title="Syracuse">Syracuse</a> and its beautiful baroque historical centre of Ortigia.</p>
<p><span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 6<br /></span></span>Fans of the TV series, Inspector Montalbano will have noticed the gorgeous settings which include the little towns of Scicli and Ragusa. At Scicli, you’ll see the 'Police Station' before moving onto Ragusa, the setting for fictional Vigata. Even if you’re not a fan of the show, you’ll appreciate this stunning corner of <a data-udi="umb://document/b037a20c14a3421ba33b32859c9e3344" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b037a20c14a3421ba33b32859c9e3344}" title="Sicily">Sicily</a> that’s been listed as an UNESCO World Heritage site.</p>
<span> <img src="/media/13067823/cycling-holidays-in-the-lakes-and-mountains-inghams.jpg" alt="View of the rooftops in Ragusa, Sicily" data-udi="umb://media/3d447fcd145244e793fd64ab0fbc0a40" /></span><a data-udi="umb://document/61b9b813ca6d419794fd819362771320" href="/{localLink:umb://document/61b9b813ca6d419794fd819362771320}" title="Where to go cycling on an e-bike"><br /></a>
<p><span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 7<br /></span></span><span>Today, its a short drive to see the Castle of Donnafugata, home to the mafia boss in the Montalbano series, but also an interesting example of a Sicilian stately home from the 1800s. Then there’s a quick photo stop at the little seaside town of Punta Secca where Montalbano lives and swims, before enjoying a wine tasting and light lunch in a seaside location.</span></p>
<p><span><span class="geolocation-title">DAY 8<br /></span></span>Transfer to Catania airport for your return flight or pick up a hire car to extend your stay with us in Sicily.</p>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Tour Includes<br /><br /></h2>
<p>7 nights half board accommodation in a 4 star hotel<br />(3 nights near Taormina, 4 nights Modica)</p>
<p>Walking tour of Taormina</p>
<p>Excursion of Mount Etna</p>
<p>Guided tour of Ortigia, Scicli and Ragusa<br /><br /><span>Visits to Castle of Donnafugata and Punta Seca</span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
